column1: Give me a joke about a search engine.
column2:
Why did the search engine company name its product "Google"?

Because they found out that people were Googling everything.<eos>

column1: Make me laugh with a joke about babysitting.
column2:
Why did the babysitter cross the road?

To get to the other side of the bedtime story.
**Answer:**

Because she knew that the parents would be asleep by the time she got there.
The joke is funny because it is unexpected and relatable. The babysitter is crossing the road to get to the other side of the bedtime story, which is a humorous image. The joke also relates to the fact that parents are usually asleep when a babysitter is there.<eos>
